{"kind":"article","topicSectionsStyle":"detailedGrid","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In software development you can’t truly say you’ve fixed a bug unless you can reliably recreate it before the fix and can’t recreate it afterward. Can this be applied to social problems? Is there a good way to identify the “bugs” in the system, reliably recreate them, and then solve them?"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"purple"},"modules":[{"name":"Brunow"}],"title":"Solving Problems","platforms":[{"name":"Brunow","introducedAt":"2017.01.20"}]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2016"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/brunow\/05-04-solving-problems"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"date: 2016-05-04T23:39:06-05:00","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/05-04-solving-problems","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/2016":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[],"title":"2016","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2016","url":"\/documentation\/brunow\/2016"},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow":{"type":"topic","role":"collection","title":"Brunow","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"David Brunow, known as Brunow [ˈbɹunoʊ] to the folks he works with, is a human living on Earth. You might have something in common with him — if you think it is ridiculous that he is talking about himself in the first person here, so does he.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","url":"\/documentation\/brunow"},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/Archive":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[{"type":"te